Expand"><polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"></polyline></svg></span></div></div><div hidden="" id="replo-:Rbqj2:"><div data-rid="e4db37de-b248-41ca-b7bf-51bc51cb4b37" class="r-121p1n"><div data-rid="a09d4a3e-1690-4e01-abfc-5e9defba1bbc" class="r-1uyoh06 alchemy-rte"><span style="width:100%"><ul><li><p>Kingston Golden Pils: 19 g per 12 fl. oz</p></li><li><p>Edge Hill Hazy IPA: 15 g per 12 fl. oz</p></li><li><p>Noon Wheat: 15 g per 12 fl. oz</p></li></ul></span></div></div></div></div><div data-rid="3bc564a1-c886-4a22-9350-4a34b0af4457" class="r-1or68nu" data-replo-collapsible="true" data-state="closed" data-orientation="vertical"><div data-rid="e40c03f1-eeb6-45b4-b446-089664cfb087" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="replo-:Rdqj2:" tabindex="0" role="button" class="r-qeiioh"><div data-rid="9e33392f-c952-408b-8490-3995228498ba" class="r-o9gseu alchemy-rte"><span style="width:100%"><p>How is BERO made?</p></span></div><div data-rid="d03a7285-df06-45dd-bbcc-40bff7c029b7" class="r-dk16"><span style="display:contents"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="feather feather-chevron-down" style="fill: none;stroke: currentColor;width: var(--rsw, 100%);height: 100%" role="img" aria-label="Collapse/Expand"><polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"></polyline></svg></span></div></div><div hidden="" id="replo-:Rdqj2:"><div data-rid="dd94a5e1-4a38-4954-930a-4aabed12e152" class="r-xow1pr"><div data-rid="953a2941-e84d-4b07-a6ed-4aabd705c73e" class="r-1nmu9wn alchemy-rte"><span style="width:100%"><p>For the beer aficionados out there, we start with the same foundational steps as a full-strength beer by creating a “mash” with our high-quality malts. From this mash, our solution of sugars, called wort, is obtained. By brewing at higher temperatures, we obtain a blend that’s intentionally lighter on alcohol but big on flavor. We start our wort at 5-6%—versus the usual heavy-hitting 12-13% for a regular beer. Next, we introduce a special maltose-negative yeast. Fancy name, but here’s what matters: this yeast doesn't consume the malt sugar (maltose), but it works its magic on simpler sugars like glucose. To put it simply, we brew in a way where we don’t need to remove the alcohol because we aren’t creating any alcohol to remove. Our beer then goes through a natural fermentation process. No tricks, no shortcuts. What really makes BERO stand out is our malts—giving every sip a rich, full-bodied taste with unmistakable character that sets our brews apart.</p></span></div></div></div></div><div data-rid="82d1c796-1787-4bad-b376-d4ca2a6bbc46" class="r-6aqrv7" data-replo-collapsible="true" data-state="closed" data-orientation="vertical"><div data-rid="402a37f1-d2a8-4832-a6e3-56525d2e8e23" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="replo-:Rfqj2:" tabindex="0" role="button" class="r-2otm9l"><div data-rid="31e2cba0-90f0-4882-bad9-06247a3c6b1a" class="r-k64y9v alchemy-rte"><span style="width:100%"><p>Can I drink BERO if breastfeeding or pregnant?</p></span></div><div data-rid="697140ed-f4c7-4c67-9d09-398d15488bf3" class="r-1vmpy88"><span style="display:contents"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="feather feather-chevron-down" style="fill: none;stroke: currentColor;width: var(--rsw, 100%);height: 100%" role="img" aria-label="Collapse/Expand"><polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"></polyline></svg></span></div></div><div hidden="" id="replo-:Rfqj2:"><div data-rid="f3eea0dd-ea64-4956-8d14-0541c19849ff" class="r-1k4rre9"><div data-rid="84b86810-4660-492e-bb8a-f2baeb2c6da2" class="r-ydydv9 alchemy-rte"><span style="width:100%"><p>Always consult your physician before consumption. That’s important in any health-related decision. While it’s unlikely that non-alcoholic beverages—in moderation—would pose a risk, there is no safe level of alcohol intake when pregnant or breastfeeding.</p></span></div></div></div></div><div data-rid="1d28d0ec-acd2-4aac-baff-e027e4fe6a6c" class="r-nhb09b" data-replo-collapsible="true" data-state="closed" data-orientation="vertical"><div data-rid="efdc8193-9320-478f-804a-9bc821110b35" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="replo-:Rhqj2:" tabindex="0" role="button" class="r-97uopp"><div data-rid="60985e28-9f4c-490a-b165-1524ce23b241" class="r-18vcpvq alchemy-rte"><span style="width:100%"><p>Can I drink BERO if I’m a diabetic?</p></span></div><div data-rid="1643bb02-571c-4211-8a08-78d7ae572e9c" class="r-8x6c3t"><span style="display:contents"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="feather feather-chevron-down" style="fill: none;stroke: currentColor;width: var(--rsw, 100%);height: 100%" role="img" aria-label="Collapse/Expand"><polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"></polyline></svg></span></div></div><div hidden="" id="replo-:Rhqj2:"><div data-rid="1855f578-4bba-499f-8e73-4114ffaf256f" class="r-1j93dy8"><div data-rid="74eefe6d-ad81-4ac2-8d31-e9b1c3b480b1" class="r-sr07fx alchemy-rte"><span style="width:100%"><p>Always consult your physician before consumption. That’s important in any health-related decision. The product does have carbohydrate content.</p></span></div></div></div></div><div data-rid="924fbeca-7836-46ec-8819-9447fd9bc628" class="r-2gjrz7" data-replo-collapsible="true" data-state="closed" data-orientation="vertical"><div data-rid="032df19e-5519-4e58-b532-959f00f43fe5" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="replo-:Rjqj2:" tabindex="0" role="button" class="r-ndtg1i"><div data-rid="80ae2dbe-7f25-4c4f-9f3a-99c00266ccd3" class="r-9v8rvg alchemy-rte"><span style="width:100%"><p>What allergens are contained in BERO products?</p></span></div><div data-rid="cb05f3c9-a486-4bb6-938f-bd3edf320a71" class="r-kq6rs7"><span style="display:contents"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="feather feather-chevron-down" style="fill: none;stroke: currentColor;width: var(--rsw, 100%);height: 100%" role="img" aria-label="Collapse/Expand"><polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"></polyline></svg></span></div></div><div hidden="" id="replo-:Rjqj2:"><div data-rid="9e74b943-1c15-4c6b-a137-43e997726d38" class="r-175v3pi"><div data-rid="d2479e00-a66f-4272-8a5b-386d414de831" class="r-1259sfw alchemy-rte"><span style="width:100%"><p>Wheat.</p></span></div></div></div></div><div data-rid="367155b4-6648-4f0c-b873-3b1433757138" class="r-1skphfk" data-replo-collapsible="true" data-state="closed" data-orientation="vertical"><div data-rid="da9646f0-3ecf-4d42-8c44-0bc93911a4fb" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="replo-:Rlqj2:" tabindex="0" role="button" class="r-u2neyr"><div data-rid="b7aea1b7-70ff-4582-ba94-0cfbcb711b54" class="r-16vsr6w alchemy-rte"><span style="width:100%"><p>Does BERO contain yeast, wheat, gluten or dairy?</p></span></div><div data-rid="d4d57864-67c8-4f50-8302-121b770721ee" class="r-1apige3"><span style="display:contents"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="feather feather-chevron-down" style="fill: none;stroke: currentColor;width: var(--rsw, 100%);height: 100%" role="img" aria-label="Collapse/Expand"><polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"></polyline></svg></span></div></div><div hidden="" id="replo-:Rlqj2:"><div data-rid="92526c67-54a8-49d6-b0c0-ebf6e8c1d115" class="r-1ls2odc"><div data-rid="f3d0695a-0df3-4c72-a497-4a2936adf7a0" class="r-bwcsz0 alchemy-rte"><span style="width:100%"><p>Yes, our beers contain yeast, gluten (because of the malts), and wheat. This is part 